                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1205">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/34208: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-12T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 12, 1944—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1646. For Tittmann. Competent authorities state that you should as heretofore
                    continue to notify us immediately by telegraph of Vatican’s advance notices to
                    you of departures of its convoys (Bern’s 2948, May 10—your 163, May 3). Such
                    action on your part will not constitute guarantee of desired immunity but your
                    telegrams will be relayed to the competent Allied Commander for his
                    information.</p>
                <p>For your own secret information, competent authorities do not wish to prescribe
                    any rules as to how much advance notice Vatican should give in such cases.
                    However, you will understand that unavoidable delays in the transmission and
                    relaying of your telegrams make it desirable to have as long a notice as
                    possible in each case.</p>
                <p>Sent to Bern; repeated to Algiers.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
